          "role": "assistant",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "reasoning",
              "is_native": true,
              "reasoning": "Done! Let me give the user a summary.",
              "signature": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Done! Here's what I created:\n\n### Prisma Schema\n```prisma\nmodel Category {\n  id, name, slug, icon, isActive, products[]\n}\n\nmodel Product {\n  id, name, slug, description, price, stock, thumbnail, isActive, categoryId\n}\n```\n\n### Backend Modules\n\n**Supabase Module** (`src/supabase/`)\n- `uploadFile()` - Upload to bucket\n- `deleteFile()` - Delete from bucket\n\n**Category Module** (`src/category/`)\n- `GET /api/categories` - List all\n- `GET /api/categories/:id` - Get one\n- `POST /api/categories` - Create\n- `PUT /api/categories/:id` - Update\n- `DELETE /api/categories/:id` - Delete\n\n**Product Module** (`src/product/`)\n- `GET /api/products` - List all (optional `?categoryId=`)\n- `GET /api/products/:id` - Get one\n- `POST /api/products` - Create (multipart with `thumbnail` file)\n- `PUT /api/products/:id` - Update (multipart with `thumbnail` file)\n- `DELETE /api/products/:id` - Delete (also removes thumbnail from storage)\n\n### Now push schema to database:\n```bash\ncd backend\npnpm prisma db push\npnpm prisma generate\n```\n\nThen restart the backend server.",
              "signature": null
            }
          ],
