              "type": "reasoning",
              "is_native": true,
              "reasoning": "The user wants:\n1. Header height same as sidebar header height (sidebar header has `h-9` button in a `p-3` div, so it's about 36px + 24px padding = ~60px, but looking at mobile sidebar header it's `h-12`)\n2. Remove the logo from the header\n\nThe sidebar header has a search button inside `p-3` div with `h-9` button. The header currently has `h-12`.\n\nLet me check the sidebar header height:\n- Desktop sidebar: `p-3` div containing `h-9` button = 12px + 36px + 12px = 60px total\n- Mobile sidebar header: `h-12` = 48px\n\nThe header is `h-12` = 48px.\n\nLooking at it more carefully:\n- Sidebar header (search area): `border-b border-zinc-200 p-3` with `h-9` button inside = padding 12px * 2 + button 36px = 60px\n- Header: `h-12` = 48px\n\nSo they don't match. I should make the header match the sidebar header. Let me make it consistent - I'll use the same height for both.\n\nActually, the sidebar search is in a div with `p-3` and a button of `h-9`. Let me calculate:\n- p-3 = padding 12px top and bottom = 24px total\n- h-9 = 36px\n- Total = 60px? No wait, the button is inside the padding.\n\nActually with `p-3`, it's 12px padding on all sides. The button is h-9 (36px). So the total height is 12 + 36 + 12 = 60px.\n\nBut the mobile sidebar header is `h-12` (48px).\n\nLet me just make the sidebar search area have a fixed height like `h-[60px]` and the header also `h-[60px]`.\n\nI'll standardize both components to use the same height value and remove the logo from the header in the process.",
              "signature": ""
            }
